Parliament, Tuesday, 4 May 2021 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow visit Makana Local Municipality as part of its oversight visit to the Eastern Cape municipalities.
	
	The committee will get a progress report from the municipality on the Auditor-General’s findings for the 2018/19 financial year, and on investigations that include the Special Investigating Unit reports.
	
	Details of the programme are as follows: 
	Date: Wednesday, 5 May 2021
	Time: 11:00
	Venue: Makana Local Municipality (Makhanda)
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.
	
	For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer:
	
